TYPE ERROR: Default body of 'mk' in interface 'Mk' pins the method's quantified type variable(s) 'b': the declared type 'a -> b' promises every caller its own choice of 'b', but this body fixes them to specific types. A caller instantiating them differently would get a value of the wrong type — or, if the pinned type carries an effect row, a value typed pure that silently performs effects. Make the body parametric in 'b', or name the intended concrete type in the method's signature.